WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.775 --> 00:09.522
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.182 --> 00:18.353
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.473 --> 00:27.986
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:29.154 --> 00:34.901
The heroic in Christianity, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part five.

00:36.383 --> 00:40.428
For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye?

00:40.488 --> 00:44.053
For sinners also love those that love them.

00:44.093 --> 00:49.980
And if ye do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye?

00:50.020 --> 00:53.184
For sinners also do even the same.

00:53.224 --> 00:57.810
And if ye lend to them of whom ye hope to receive,

00:58.178 --> 00:59.319
What thank have ye?

00:59.359 --> 01:05.187
For sinners also lend to sinners, to receive as much again.

01:06.488 --> 01:10.033
Luke's Gospel, chapter 6, verses 32 to 34.

01:10.133 --> 01:18.644
The next verse of this 17th chapter shows us that Christians are to be people of service.

01:19.264 --> 01:26.994
They are not to think that they came into the world to sit at a banquet, but they are to wait on their master while he sits at the table.

01:28.066 --> 01:33.955
Too many appear to consider that the services of the sanctuary are intended merely to feed them.

01:33.995 --> 01:42.187
They never look upon the house of God as a barracks for soldiers, or a place where workmen come together to sharpen their tools.

01:43.069 --> 01:54.105
They only regard it as a sacred restaurant, a spiritual larder, or a heavenly refectory, where much is to be received and little or nothing returned.

01:55.487 --> 01:57.170
O brothers and sisters,

01:57.506 --> 02:05.096
We must get out of the cramping influence of the spirit which makes even religion a selfish provision for ourselves.

02:06.037 --> 02:14.688
And we must scorn that skulking away from the trouble and fatigue which creeps over men of growing years and increasing wealth.

02:15.650 --> 02:19.555
We are to serve, not to recline at our ease.

02:20.876 --> 02:25.202
What are we that are so anxious to rest ourselves and benefit ourselves?

02:26.082 --> 02:31.468
The Lord Jesus Christ would not have us always be asking, how can I be happy?

02:32.188 --> 02:34.911
How can I obtain spiritual enjoyment?

02:35.972 --> 02:41.738
Servants are not supposed to spend their time in doing their own pleasure and seeking their own profit.

02:42.859 --> 02:50.007
A man's servant whose whole time was taken up with watching his own health would be of small value to his employer.

02:51.188 --> 02:53.330
Even so we have something else to do

02:53.538 --> 02:56.602
beyond watching over our own inward feelings.

02:57.544 --> 03:02.511
To snatch a brand from the burning is better than to warm your own hands.

03:03.592 --> 03:13.206
To feed a hungry soul with the bread of heaven is a far higher deed than to eat the fat and drink the sweet yourself.

03:14.348 --> 03:21.618
There is more joy in plunging your arm up to the elbow in the mire to find a jewel for Christ.

03:21.986 --> 03:28.115
than in washing one's own idle hands with the scented soap of respectable propriety.

03:29.818 --> 03:34.665
Oh, to get clean away from all idea of self-seeking in religion.

03:36.207 --> 03:48.626
We are first of all saved by grace, like drowning mariners snatched from the deep, but afterwards we are taught to man the lifeboat ourselves for the rescue of others from destruction.

03:49.858 --> 03:55.386
Christianity finds me a soldier wounded in battle and it heals my wounds.

03:56.328 --> 03:58.030
But it does far more than that.

03:58.571 --> 04:09.147
It girds me with armor, it gives me a sword, it teaches me to fight, and it makes a hero of me if I yield myself to its full power.

04:10.388 --> 04:13.633
God grant it may do this for every one of us.

04:15.436 --> 04:19.602
I will now close with the reflection that the Christian religion

04:20.130 --> 04:23.994
Supplies due nourishment for the most heroic life.

04:25.296 --> 04:27.979
Bear with me while I show you this in a few sentences.

04:29.180 --> 04:33.025
First, the economy of grace requires it.

04:34.426 --> 04:43.457
You and I must have been chosen to lead a life higher than that of ordinary men, or else why all this noise and stir at all?

04:44.598 --> 04:48.082
We see heaven and earth and hell in motion

04:48.962 --> 04:52.405
God vacates his throne and becomes a man.

04:53.226 --> 04:57.110
Immortality puts on flesh and blood and dies.

04:58.031 --> 05:04.538
The Holy Spirit comes to dwell in these bodies of clay, while angels look on and wonder.

05:05.939 --> 05:10.724
Surely here is the groundwork and argument of something supremely good.

05:12.586 --> 05:17.010
See you that angel bright and sparkling like a flame of fire.

05:17.538 --> 05:20.382
What trouble did it cost the Creator to make Him?

05:20.403 --> 05:23.908
A thought sufficed to do it.

05:25.070 --> 05:33.403
God willed it, and there stood the helmed cherubim and sordid seraphim before Him in all their glittering ranks.

05:35.286 --> 05:40.073
What will that creature be, which has been the subject of eternal purposes?

05:41.195 --> 05:45.522
Which has cost the Father the heart-paying of giving up His only Son?

05:45.666 --> 06:14.418
cost the sun a bloody sweat cost the spirit the exercise of his omnipotence such a creature you and I shall yet become we are on the road to it great things ought to come of us if that is what we are and are growing to may this thought nourish us to the highest life think again brethren we are helped

06:14.530 --> 06:18.615
to holy heroism by the reward which it brings.

06:19.476 --> 06:28.708
For our blessed master, though he bids us spurn the thought of reward on earth, yet tells us that there is a reward in the thing itself.

06:29.689 --> 06:32.632
Just follow my text in the 35th verse.

06:33.513 --> 06:41.503
Love ye your enemies and do good and lend, hoping for nothing again, and your reward shall be great.

06:42.765 --> 06:43.666
What reward?

06:44.706 --> 06:46.929
why the reward of having done good.

06:47.971 --> 06:49.033
This is quite enough.

06:50.195 --> 07:03.075
If you go to your brother who has treated you so badly and say, brother, we are going to be friends and you manage to heal all wounds, you will not want any other reward.

07:04.136 --> 07:10.506
You will sleep sweetly at night and the music that awakes you in the morning will be sweet as the bells of heaven.

07:11.548 --> 07:12.850
Suppose you have an enemy.

07:13.186 --> 07:16.290
and persistently do him all the good you can.

07:16.330 --> 07:19.114
You will not wish to be paid for it.

07:20.256 --> 07:26.825
It is such a grand thing to have acted like a Christian that you will be blessed in the deed.

07:28.647 --> 07:42.066
I believe that martyrs at the stake, when they stood and burned for Christ, felt in every pang a thousand times rewarded by possessing the grace which enabled them to endure to the end.

07:43.266 --> 07:50.417
they felt, we are doing the right thing, we are testifying to the truth of our beloved Lord.

07:52.259 --> 07:58.488
And if they had possessed a thousand lives, they would cheerfully have laid down all for Jesus.

08:00.071 --> 08:10.386
Therefore do not miss a mercenary as to expect to be paid in dirty bronze and tarnished silver, but ask to find your recompense

08:10.594 --> 08:17.041
in the Spirit by which you are led to do good, and in the smile of your heavenly Father.

08:18.683 --> 08:21.907
Then mark you this to fire your ambition.

08:22.508 --> 08:24.850
You shall be children of the highest.

08:26.032 --> 08:30.937
Those who can rise into the heroic life shall be as God.

08:32.018 --> 08:38.706
The gentle, patient, peaceable, kind, loving, forgiving, affectionate,

08:39.426 --> 08:42.989
These shall be known to be the sons and daughters of God.

08:44.130 --> 08:45.231
And is this nothing?

08:45.251 --> 08:54.820
Oh, if there is a grain of nobility in your natures, you will make this the highest ambition of your lives to be like God.

08:56.082 --> 08:57.543
What is more than that?

08:59.124 --> 09:03.388
We are expected to be like God because we are His children.

09:04.449 --> 09:09.394
He shall be the children of the highest, for He is kind unto the unthankful.

09:09.890 --> 09:10.831
and to the evil.

09:12.053 --> 09:15.438
We expect to see something of the Father in the child.

09:16.239 --> 09:21.106
If we are children of God, we ought to do what others never think of.

09:23.029 --> 09:30.880
If you are the children of God, remember what a brother you have, and what an example he has set you.

09:32.242 --> 09:37.810
He disdained to live unto himself, for he left the throne of glory,

09:37.890 --> 09:45.197
to come down to Bethlehem's manger, to a carpenter's shop, to a servant's life.

09:46.959 --> 09:52.644
The other night, I heard read at family prayer the story of our Lord at the supper table.

09:53.665 --> 10:04.055
Jesus knowing that he came from God and went to God, took a towel and girded himself and began to wash his disciples' feet.

10:05.597 --> 10:06.898
Ah, when I thought of him,

10:07.202 --> 10:16.152
whom all heaven worships, our blessed, blessed master, actually coming round with a basin to wash the disciples' feet.

10:17.454 --> 10:25.723
I felt my eyes fill with tears, and I sympathized with Peter when he cried, Does thou wash my feet?

10:27.545 --> 10:34.433
It seemed a stoop too great for our Lord and King, thus to act a menial part.

10:34.453 --> 10:35.314
Is there anything

10:35.618 --> 10:41.066
which can seem too mean for you and me, after beholding such condescension.

10:42.368 --> 10:46.754
If that sight touch you not, let me remind you of a further scene.

10:47.335 --> 10:55.125
He went into Gethsemane, and there he knelt and prayed for you and me, until he was covered with a gory sweat.

10:56.087 --> 10:59.692
And great drops of blood followed each other to the ground.

11:01.034 --> 11:04.018
Is there any pain that we would not face?

11:04.578 --> 11:10.424
Is there any reproach we could not bear after this for his dear sake?

11:11.705 --> 11:13.126
Does not that rouse you?

11:13.146 --> 11:21.674
Will you after this be proud and claim honor of your brethren and grow angry if it be refused?

11:21.694 --> 11:26.839
Come with me once again for he goes to the cross and there he hangs.

11:28.280 --> 11:29.822
It is your Lord, remember.

11:31.263 --> 11:34.226
See the iron passes through his hand.

11:35.266 --> 11:37.529
It is your Lord who is thus maimed.

11:39.212 --> 11:43.718
The nails tear through his feet, the feet of your Lord.

11:45.000 --> 11:49.247
He wears a crown as monarch, but it is a coronet of thorns.

11:50.228 --> 11:52.952
It is your Lord who is thus crowned.

11:54.554 --> 12:00.343
He wears crimson too, but it is his own blood, and he is your own Lord.

12:01.525 --> 12:05.170
He has not a rag else, for they have stripped him

12:05.826 --> 12:09.332
Yes, stripped and scourged your Lord.

12:10.794 --> 12:16.183
And they are hissing at him, jesting at his prayers and scoffing at his cries.

12:17.285 --> 12:19.288
All this at your Lord.

12:20.850 --> 12:21.592
And what of you?

12:21.632 --> 12:27.902
The other day you were so ashamed to own that you were his disciple.

12:29.505 --> 12:32.850
Are you not disgusted at such cowardice?

12:34.082 --> 12:37.687
You were silent the other day when sinners were blaspheming him.

12:38.868 --> 12:43.494
You were stingy when his poor people needed help.

12:43.514 --> 12:48.600
You refused to give when his church and his cause knocked at your door.

12:50.863 --> 13:02.578
You would not forgive a fellow Christian the other day and you parted company with one who had been your friend for years and all for a hot word.

13:03.554 --> 13:06.739
And yet, you call yourself a Christian.

13:08.421 --> 13:15.211
Yes, and I too am a Christian and have my own private cause for self humiliation.

13:17.094 --> 13:20.299
And that is our master bleeding there.

13:21.661 --> 13:24.085
How can we bear to look him in the face?

13:25.387 --> 13:27.390
What sorry disciples we are.

13:28.251 --> 13:32.978
Oh blessed master, let thy blood drop on us

13:33.218 --> 13:38.704
until thou hast blotted out these many faults of ours and made us like thyself.

13:40.386 --> 13:42.548
Amen and Amen.

13:43.710 --> 13:44.991
Thank you for listening, friends.

13:45.271 --> 13:50.057
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

13:50.657 --> 13:58.706
